Police have detained a female suspect following an attack on the U.S. consulate building in Istanbul on August 10. Two attackers opened fire on the U.S. consulate building in Turkey\'s biggest city, and fled when police shot back. Local media said those involved in the attack on the building included one man and one woman. Turkey has been in a heightened state of alert since it launched what officials described as a \"synchronised war on terror\" last month, including air strikes against Islamic State fighters in Syria and Kurdish militants in northern Iraq. 
U.S. diplomatic missions have been targeted in Turkey in the past.

